public void OnTick()

AfterTick

public void AfterTick()
Called at the end of every synchronised tick, this is used in rare circumstances, such as measuring latency or tick times.

OnStartRender

public void OnStartRender()
Called at the start of every render tick, this is used in rare circumstances, such as measuring render times. Anything drawn here will likely be drawn over later.

OnRender

public void OnRender()
Called at the end of every render tick, this is the main method used to add a custom render item to the game, since this will be on top of everything else.

RunOnce

public void RunOnce()
Called once before the main @see MojamComponent game loop. Used for initialising scripts, since mods can use their constructors.

OnClose

public void OnClose()
Called when the window is closed, used for shutting down scripts.

public void OnSendPacket(Packet packet)

OnVictory

Parameters:

OnLevelTick

public void OnLevelTick(Level level)
Called whenever the level itself ticks, such as respawning spawners or spawning mobs. This can be used to manipulate the world in all sorts of ways.

Parameters:
level - The @see Level being ticked

OnReceivePacket

Parameters:
packet - The @see Packet being received over the network

CreateLevel

getEntityInstanceById

public Entity getEntityInstanceById(int i,
                                    double x,
                                    double y)
Called whenever an entity is spawned. It cycles through loaded mods, and until it is returned an entity. Use it in conjunction with the i value and registering entities so that @code{ if(i==myEntityId)return new MyEntity(i,x,y); }

Parameters:
i - The id of the Entity to spawn
x - The x location of the new Entity to Spawn
y - the y location of the new Entity to Spawn
Returns:
A new instance of your registered entity
